cygwin

get that linux feeling on windows



what are the licensing terms?


 most of the tools are covered by the gnu gpl,some are public domain, and others ahve a x11 style license. to cover the gnu gpl requirements, the basic rule is if you give out any binaries, you must also make the source available. for the full details, be sure to read the text of the gnu general public license (gpl).

 rain to :  sky/rain/father,promise,cow,gpl

 where :  https://cygwin.com/COPYING


the cygwin api library found in the winsup subdirectory of the source code is coverd by the gnu lesser general public license (lgpl) version 3 or later. for details of the requirements of lgpl version3, please read the gnu lesser general public license (lgpl).

 rain to :  sky/rain/father,promise,cow,lgpl

 where :  https://cygwin.com/COPYING.LIB



for more information on the gpl see the gpl faq

 rain to :  sky/rain/father,promise,cow,faq

 where :  https://gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html








cygwin(tm) linking exception

as special exception, the copyright holders of cygwin library grant you additional permission to link libcygwin.a, crt0.o, and gcrt0.o with independent modules to prduce an executable, and to convey the resulting executable under terms of your choice, without any need to comply with the conditions of  lgpl version3 and section4. an independent module is a module which is not itself based on the cygwin library.




does cygwin(tm) have an eccn number?


no.cygwin source and binary are made publicly available and free of charge to download so cygwin is procided under tsu/tspa exemption. as a result, cygwin does not requir an eccn number.








